---
// The diner storefront `/` — a DELIBERATE STUB (T-062-01-02, decision (b)).
//
// This page renders a placeholder ON PURPOSE. The menu itself is the slice `vend work`
// clears: read the couple's `Dish` content from EmDash's REST API and render an appetizing,
// mobile-first menu here (one card per dish: photo, name, description). Until that drive,
// `/` honestly says "coming soon" — no dishes, no EmDash fetch, no fake demand (IA-4).
//
// Mobile-first by design (the diner opens this on a phone): a single centered column,
// system font, fluid padding. Keep it dependency-free so the stub builds green standalone.
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <title>Our Kitchen — menu coming soon</title>
  </head>
  <body style="margin: 0; min-height: 100vh; display: flex; background: #fff8f2; font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif; color: #2b2b2b;">
    <main style="margin: auto; max-width: 28rem; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; text-align: center;">
      <p style="font-size: 3rem; margin: 0;" aria-hidden="true">🍳</p>
      <h1 style="margin: 0.5rem 0 0; font-size: 1.75rem; line-height: 1.2;">
        Our kitchen menu is coming soon
      </h1>
      <p style="color: #6b6258; margin: 1rem 0 0; line-height: 1.5;">
        Add your dishes in the EmDash admin — photo, name, and a short description — then let
        <strong>vend</strong> build this menu. One card per dish, made for the phone you’re
        holding.
      </p>
      <p style="color: #a89c8e; font-size: 0.875rem; margin: 2rem 0 0;">
        This page is a starting point, not the finished menu.
      </p>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
